### 4. Update of Service and Network YANG Data Models
* **Presentation**: [04) An Update of Service and Network YANG Data Models](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-onsen-an-update-of-service-and-network-yang-data-models-00)
* **Presenter**: Oscar de Dios
* **Discussion**: This work compiles concrete implementation requirements for the network model layer (the layer below customer service). Proposed enhancements include additions for BFD, billing, ACLs, SRv6, and multicast. It also addresses the definition of operational status (distinguishing between "configuration deployment success" and "active network failures").
  * *Joe Clarke* encouraged the authors to move fast on these concrete updates, as operators need them immediately, even if broader architectural questions take longer to resolve.
  * *Ian Farrer* clarified that the draft currently serves to compile requirements and includes some code.
  * *Italo Busi* inquired if the SRv6 extensions map to specific SR policies. Oscar de Dios clarified it is simpler—it indicates whether a node needs to operate with SRv6. Italo Busi also asked if multi-controller environments are considered; Oscar de Dios noted the current scope is limited to a single administrative domain.

